description.2: Kitty defeats Gravemoss in Nightcrawler's body while Shrill separates the two entities!
description.3: Agamemnon's trial is cut short by the arrival of the mysterious Eternal Knights! Will their arrival mean the end of the Pantheon? And what is this startling new transformation for the Hulk?
description.4: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Iron Man's final confrontation with the Mandarin! Will Iron Man, War Machine, and their allies be able to defeat their evil enemy once and for all?
description.5: Vikady, one of the Russian criminals at stake, attempts to sell a nuclear weapon...and it's up to the Punisher to stop him! Will the United Nations get in his way?
description.7: Thor, Don Blake, Jane Foster, the High Evolutionary, and the Godpack head to space to battle the New Immortals and the New Men!
description.10: Susan's in the spotlight! Still believing Reed to be alive somewhere, the Invisible Woman goes it alone on a stealth mission to Latveria!
description.11: While battling Legion in the Negev Desert, the X-Men are transported back in time!
description.12: Sabretooth makes an unwanted appearance! Wolverine and Ghost Rider face a supernatural threat when the ghost of Ogun returns. But why has Ogun's spirit not been laid to rest?
description.16: Can Cannonball accept the fact that his own sister is going to be trained by his former enemy, Emma Frost? Meanwhile, a mysterious masked figure is stalking the halls of the Verschlagen facility in Germany…
description.18: Dormammu nearly lures Clea back to the Dark Dimension. The Strangers’ influence takes its toll.
description.20: Bova's husband Fydor, transformed into a beast! Quicksilver, Crystal, and the High Evolutionary must spring into action after Exodus' plot is revealed. At Avengers Mansion, the immortal Hera reveals herself as Taylor Madison, Hercules' mortal love interest!
description.22: New arc…new Secret Defenders! This time, joining the team are Drax the Destroyer, Deathlok, and Dagger!
description.24: The family stares down the threat of the demon Lenz, while clan patriarch Adam Destine returns from his cosmic journey!
description.26: Guest-starring Peter Parker… and the Daily Bugle's Betty Brant! In the aftermath to his wife and children's murder, Frank Castle places his misguided trust in the police… who prove to do little about his case. Castle has hit his boiling point, and the Punisher threatens to emerge.
description.30: The'Empire'in retreat,'Luke Skywalker'has begun a quest to rebuild the'Jedi. Although dead, the'Emperor's presence still haunts him, and Luke still feels the taint of the'dark side'from his time as the Emperor's thrall.
description.31: Leia uncovers a dark secret about the Imperial labor force. Finding herself a Rebel amongst Imperials, Leia can either play it safe or make a move! Will the princess be able to escape the clutches of the Empire?
description.32: The Krath attack! During a seemingly peaceful meeting of the Jedi Knights, a deadly blow is struck for the dark side of the Force! The first casualties of this struggle between dark and light galvanize Ulic toward a rash decision that may cost him his life.
description.34: Bishop and Storm’s night at the theater is interrupted when Bishop's old acquaintance Bantam approaches them - with a malicious mutant named Mountjoy on his tail!
description.35: The war for Monster Isle continues! Tyrannus is more than a match for the Infinity Watch, but perhaps the tables can turn when the Mole Man comes to their aid!
description.36: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Mandarin confronts his past! Note: this issue contains only the Force Works story.
description.45: Gravemoss in the body of Nightcrawler attacks the rest of Excalibur!
description.46: The Trial of Agamemnon! The former ally of the Pantheon has been planting secret machinations for years, and now, all those secrets will come to life in a way that will change the Hulk forever!
description.47: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Iron Man has been captured by the Mandarin! Can War Machine and Force Works save Iron Man from the deadly villain's torture chamber?
description.48: Frank Castle discovers that a pack of Russian mobsters are carrying something a far more dangerous than heroin...
description.50: Thor and the Godpack fight off the Living Rock to save the Earth's surface from mass destruction!
description.52: A grudge match 20 issues in the making! In a previous battle, Wolverine scarred Ben Grimm's face with his adamantium claws - now, the Thing wants payback! It's up to the Astonishing Ant-Man to break up this heroes' quarrel before it turns ugly!
description.53: Iceman and Rogue travel to Iceman's home. Meanwhile, a romance between Pyslocke and Archangel blooms.
description.57: The High Evolutionary calls off the New Men's attack, but demands to know why Quicksilver has returned to Wundagore. After sharing news of Bova's illness, the Evolutionary formulates a "cure". But will Pietro's arch-nemesis provide the help Bova so desperately needs?
description.58: Cuckoo uses her powers to inhabit the body of Pepa Perez! Also, a surprise guest appearance from the Silver Surfer!
description.63: The Spirit of Vengeance, the eternal soldier, and the very best there is! Ghost Rider, Punisher, and Wolverine unite to stop the darkness of Blackheart with the baddest hero team-up in comics!
description.64: It's a new beginning for one of the Secret Defenders! Shadow Woman is no more…long live the newest Secret Defender, SEPULCHRE!
description.66: The truth is revealed about the murder mysteries of the Callasantos family! Which Callasantos sister will prove to be innocent? Maria? Lucia? Neither?
description.69: Strange is bonded with the Aetheric Sword! Salome’s final hour fast approaches once the Doctor is equipped with the full power of the Gaian Aura.
description.71: We've known for years about the deaths of Frank Castle's wife and children, but now we see Castle himself mere hours later, when his grief and rage were at their freshest. To the police, he's a lead. To a reporter, he's a story. To the mob, he's just one more loose end. Relive the brutal origin of the Punisher, told in vivid detail by Dan Abnett, Andy Lanning and Dale Eaglesham!
description.75: War comes to Monster Isle! The conquering Tyrannus has come to seize the isle for himself, and only the Infinity Watch can stop him! Meanwhile, has Drax actually managed to make new friends?
description.76: A special one-shot featuring Thing, Doctor Strange, Human Torch and more!
description.86: With the power of the dark side of the Force aiding them, Satal and Aleema -- two wealthy young aristocrats -- boldly begin annexing the galaxy! Alerted to this deadly threat to peace, the Jedi begin planning a defense... but will they be too late? Against this backdrop of interstellar war, Ulic Qel-Droma and Nomi Sunrider -- two novice Jedi Knights -- find that in the heat of war, there can be flames of passion!
description.87: Luke is told to abandon a rescue mission by the Rebel Command. But will Skywalker follow his heroic nature and defy orders instead? An exciting Rebel development on Tatooine brings Luke back to his homeplanet!
description.90: The fight in Slorenia takes a surprising turn, when Force Works is suddenly betrayed by the Slorenian Black Brigade! Can the team survive a two-pronged atttack?
description.91: The Fantastic Four are no more! With the First Family split, Franklin Richards is left wondering how to fill the void. With the help of friends Huntara, Black Panther, Devlor, and Vibraxas, Franklin can pick up where the original team has left off- as Psi-Lord, member of the all-new FANTASTIC FORCE!
description.93: The battle with Slaymaker reaches an explosive and unbelievable climax!
description.95: Learn the wild origins of the ancient (and eternal) ClanDestine family! These super powered Brits have a lineage that dates back to 1168 A.D.!
description.96: Psionex ramps up the attack against a strained New Warriors squad.
description.99: Guest-starring Rick Jones! Hulk’s oldest ally helps get Stevens out of the Hulk. The Vishanti pay a visit to Salome.

0.text: Beast and Phoenix are ambushed by the Dark Riders!

1.text: A battle amongst Daredevil, Bushwacker, Devourer and Deathlok breaks out.  Meanwhile, Jenkins threatens Ed and Ralphie and makes them confess to the bombings.

8.text: The Grim Hunter catches the Scarlet Spider's scent!

9.text: Extraterrestrials are on the loose in Madripoor! Thankfully, X-Factor is on hand to help.

13.text: Legion captures and blasts the X-Men 20 years into the past!

16.text: Can Cannonball accept the fact that his own sister is going to be trained by his former enemy, Emma Frost? Meanwhile, a mysterious masked figure is stalking the halls of the Verschlagen facility in Germany…

18.text: Dormammu nearly lures Clea back to the Dark Dimension. The Strangers’ influence takes its toll.

21.text: Eddie finds himself captive of five symbiotes – begging for his help!

22.text: New arc…new Secret Defenders! This time, joining the team are Drax the Destroyer, Deathlok, and Dagger!

25.text: Captain America and Iron Man star in this thrilling reboot of the 1959 series! S.H.I.E.L.D. may need help against D.A.N.T.E., an off the books, diabolical agency.

27.text: Margaretta von Geisterstadt proves her mettle when she toys with the mind of Doom!

28.text: Venom and Spider-Man confront the past (and present) of the Life Foundation... including its villainous byproducts!

33.text: Generation X tries to figure out who the mysterious mutant Penance really is, and Gateway isn’t talking. Is the razor-sharp newcomer friend or foe?

34.text: Bishop and Storm’s night at the theater is interrupted when Bishop's old acquaintance Bantam approaches them - with a malicious mutant named Mountjoy on his tail!

35.text: The war for Monster Isle continues! Tyrannus is more than a match for the Infinity Watch, but perhaps the tables can turn when the Mole Man comes to their aid!

36.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Mandarin confronts his past! Note: this issue contains only the Force Works story.

37.text: Spider-Man's world gets turned upside-down when one of his greatest enemies turns out to be his father…

38.text: While healing from his wounds, Ben Reilly's Spider-Sense goes wild. He must don his Scarlet Spider garb and face down Venom yet again!

39.text: Wolverine pays a visit to Kane only to be greeted by Deadpool! Logan gets an unexpected handful as he deals with the barbs and blows of the Mouthy Merc!

41.text: The chase of the Dark Riders is on! Cable, Domino and Storm are on the Riders' trail when they are suddenly transported to the scene of a massacre! Who is responsible for this horror, and how is Cable's son Tyler connected to it all?

42.text: The Serpent Society steps in! But who or what is...Jack Flag?

43.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Mandarin seeks the mighty power of the Heart of Darkness! Note: this issue contains only the Force Works story.

44.text: The King sacrifices two of his subordinates which creates the Devourer.  Joshua makes Daredevil doubt himself and then both the Devourer and Bushwacker attack Daredevil.

49.text: Venom and Scarlet Spider continue their no-holds-barred battle to the death!

51.text: In Israel, Mystique lines up her sights on a new target. Only X-Factor can stop her now.

54.text: When Scott’s grandfather crashes his plane into the Canadian mountainside, an unlikely mutant comes to his aid.

59.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! The team faces off against the deadly forces of the Mandarin!

60.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! War Machine is joined by Century and the rest of Force Works as they do battle with the Mandarin’s Avatars!

61.text: After their robotic romp in New Orleans, Jocasta and Vision open a detective agency…in Chicago! The Avengers have been missing their heaviest-hitter, and send Deathcry and Crystal to retrieve Vision. But what has led to Vision’s strange turn in pace?

62.text: Venom is beaten. Eddie Brock is a captive, with no hope of ever reuniting with his precious symbiote. But little does he know that people are already planning to help him escape – but when Eddie finds out who it is, will he even want to?

63.text: The Spirit of Vengeance, the eternal soldier, and the very best there is! Ghost Rider, Punisher, and Wolverine unite to stop the darkness of Blackheart with the baddest hero team-up in comics!

64.text: It's a new beginning for one of the Secret Defenders! Shadow Woman is no more…long live the newest Secret Defender, SEPULCHRE!

65.text: On Mars, the Guardians are introduced to the interplanetary serial killer, RIPJAK!

66.text: The truth is revealed about the murder mysteries of the Callasantos family! Which Callasantos sister will prove to be innocent? Maria? Lucia? Neither?

67.text: The X-Men go their separate directions and split up! But why?

69.text: Strange is bonded with the Aetheric Sword! Salome’s final hour fast approaches once the Doctor is equipped with the full power of the Gaian Aura.

72.text: Tiger Wylde continues to trail Doom and Wire, as they attempt to reach their safe point!

74.text: Hulk, Henry Pym and the Wasp are all caught in the dastardly Loki’s dream!

75.text: War comes to Monster Isle! The conquering Tyrannus has come to seize the isle for himself, and only the Infinity Watch can stop him! Meanwhile, has Drax actually managed to make new friends?

76.text: A special one-shot featuring Thing, Doctor Strange, Human Torch and more!

78.text: The first phenomenal issue! The next generation of mutant heroes begins their training now! Who is the energy-draining Emplate, and what is his connection to M?

79.text: SINS OF THE PAST PART 4 Deadpool and his newfound allies Banshee and Siryn must bring Black Tom down! The exciting conclusion to SINS OF THE PAST is here!

80.text: Spider-Man's been keeping busy lately, Kasey's down after her fight with Alchemax, and the Flyboy cops beat up on Gabe!

81.text: Ben Reilly and Venom, unbeknownst to one another, take their own strolls down memory lane to see where it all began!

83.text: THE DARK RIDE begins here! Cable and Domino visit the X-Men, but reunions are cut short by the appearance of the Dark Riders! What are the Riders after, and who is behind their resurgence?

84.text: Cap and Free Spirit trapped by Baron Zemo! The final fate of Diamondback!

88.text: War Machine vs. Iron Man! This time it’s personal!

89.text: Vision takes center stage in the first issue of his mini-series. Avenger Vision is regarded as the ultimate creation of Ultron; an automaton of supreme intellect and intangibility. But when Vision begins to experience humanness in the form of dreams, thirst, and passion, all he knows will be challenged. Haunted by dreams that seem like memories, Vision travels to New Orleans to piece together his past.  Enter Ultron!

90.text: The fight in Slorenia takes a surprising turn, when Force Works is suddenly betrayed by the Slorenian Black Brigade! Can the team survive a two-pronged atttack?

91.text: The Fantastic Four are no more! With the First Family split, Franklin Richards is left wondering how to fill the void. With the help of friends Huntara, Black Panther, Devlor, and Vibraxas, Franklin can pick up where the original team has left off- as Psi-Lord, member of the all-new FANTASTIC FORCE!

92.text: In the midst of the battle with the Stalkers, Venom learns a startling truth about his parasitic partner!

93.text: The battle with Slaymaker reaches an explosive and unbelievable climax!

94.text: The galactic saving crew takes their adventure to Mars!

97.text: Lucia Callasantos, AKA Thornn is arrested for the murder of her family. Can Cable and Sam save her from an inevitable fate? Meanwhile, X-Force has a new home base- Murderworld!

99.text: Guest-starring Rick Jones! Hulk’s oldest ally helps get Stevens out of the Hulk. The Vishanti pay a visit to Salome.
